  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Being confronted more and more with obese as well as older patients, minimally invasive
      surgery is said to keep the surgical trauma low. The prospective long-term evaluation is the
      continuous monitoring of patients undergoing lumbar minimally invasive fusion surgery and
      analyzing the effect of body mass index (BMI) and wound healing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
